    {
      "id": "b9317115e910193b23e24039abb6dcad69802e72",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 805,
        "name": "Neil Brown",
        "email": "neil@brown.name",
        "username": "neilbrown"
      },
      "date": "2021-02-17 23:53:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nAre there any details on what sort of \"performance regressions\"?\nReads? writes? large? small? Anything?\nCPU load? Throughput? Latency?\n\nMost likely cause of behaviour change in this patch is that some merges which previously did happen, now don't happen.  Would that be likely to cause the observed performance regression?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "d7f47489cd27eab831de8f0b35c6b09f0985718f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2021-02-18 02:43:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Are there any details on what sort of \"performance regressions\"?\n > Reads? writes? large? small? Anything?\n > CPU load? Throughput? Latency?\n > \n > Most likely cause of behaviour change in this patch is that some\n > merges which previously did happen, now don't happen.  Would that\n > be likely to cause the observed performance regression?\n\nNeil, see the comments in https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14424",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "fb9b642978eaf92e9e41a399c3e55a8fe8185b13",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 805,
        "name": "Neil Brown",
        "email": "neil@brown.name",
        "username": "neilbrown"
      },
      "date": "2021-02-19 04:47:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Neil, see the comments in LU-14424\n\nYes, of course.  I should have thought of that.  Sorry.\n\nThe problem is probably that I didn't update cur->oe_state to OES_CACHE before calling osc_extent_merge().  So all merge attempts would fail.\n\nAlso, by calling osc_extent_hold() before osc_extent_merge(), I risk triggering an LASSERT() ... which probably aren't actually being checked??\n\nI'll submit a revised patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    }
  ],
